-- Russia Plans to Raise $29 Billion Selling Company Stakes, Reuters Reports
-- Stephen Bierman
-- 2010-07-25T10:54:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-25/russia-plans-to-raise-29-billion-selling-company-stakes-reuters-reports.html

          
          
             Russia has proposed raising $29
billion to plug budget gaps by selling minority stakes in 10
companies including  OAO Rosneft , the nation’s largest oil
producer, and OAO Transneft, Reuters  reported , citing people in
the Finance Ministry it didn’t identify.  
 The plan proposes selling 27.1 percent in oil pipeline
operator Transneft, 24.16 percent of Rosneft, 24.5 percent of
the bank VTB, 9.3 percent of OAO Sberbank and just under 25
percent of OAO Russian Railways, Reuters said citing the
unidentified people.  
 Other companies in which the state may offer minority
stakes include hydropower utility OAO RusHydro, Russian
Agricultural Bank, also known as Rosselkhozbank, and shipper OAO
Sovcomflot.  
